  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Environmental Control Officer (ECO)",
  "description": "<p><u>Roles and Responsibilities </u></p><ul><li>Assist and advise the Project Manager in Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) planning for both the overall project scope and specific activities.</li><li>Conduction inspection and report the conditions in construction site and provide recommendation on the remedial measures on the following area: ·      </li><li>a)      Disease-bearing insects and rodents.<br />b)      Proper disposal of construction waste<br />c)      Noise, air and water pollution.<br />d)      Earth littering<br />e)      Siltation of drain<br />f)       Food hygiene<br />g)      Proper maintenance of toilet and other sanitary facilities<br />h)      Other environment health matters. </li></ul><ul><li>Review and comply QECP checklist to ensure that the ECM is adequate. </li><li>Compile and submit environmental related data including water, electricity and diesel consumption on site, concrete wastage on site and amount of construction debris generated at site.</li><li>Compile records on any check or visiting by the Authorities (For example: NEA for noise and vectors, PUB for ECM)</li></ul><p><br /><u>Requirements:</u></p><ul><li>Minimum 3 years working experience of ECO in construction firm.</li><li>Registered ECO and ECMO qualified </li><li>Good communication skills, oral and written</li><li>Ability to work independently with high level of motivation</li><li>Hands-on, detail oriented and able to communicate effectively with all levels of staff</li><li>Positive attitude, team player and committed to continuous improvement</li><li>Certificate - Environmental Control Officer for Specified Construction Sites</li><li>Certificate - Earth Control Measure Officer</li><li>Certificate – First Aider</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
